    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "23faaebb_cf2590e4",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 13,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003065
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-21T12:40:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "@ed@tanous.net, Thanks for the comment,\n\nHere, the validator only flags things the spec explicitly forces with the word \"shall.\" The one rule about 405 (Section 7.5.3) says: if the resource exists but doesn\u0027t support the method we used, we must return 405. It never says what to return when the resource doesn\u0027t exist at all. So, returning 405 for a non-existent resource doesn\u0027t break that rule — there\u0027s no rule covering that situation, so the validator has nothing to complain about.\n\nWhy the validator misses that too:\nIt checks one request and its response at a time. It never compares two separate requests against each other to see if they agree. So, this isn\u0027t a hole in the validator\u0027s coverage — comparing two answers against each other for consistency just isn\u0027t the kind of thing it\u0027s built to test.",
      "parentUuid": "b362db15_0bf96324",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 13,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "71bedad7c8f1692d7c613474b0dfa8c4cd7c23da",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a880899b_d2595a10",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 13,
