        "id": 1003065
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-21T12:40:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Fair concern -- and it\u0027s exactly why this version drops per-resource handlers entirely. The original ManagerAccount-only handler was 61 net lines; this has 269 registered routes across 61 files, so that pattern really would scale into the thousands you\u0027re worried about.\n\nThe current fix is one generic hook in Router::handle(): it probes the URL\u0027s own GET route (privilege-gated) to pick 404 vs 405.  Total cost: 114 lines in routing.hpp, a net-0 reorder in trie.hpp, zero lines in account_service.hpp or any other endpoint file. Every future endpoint gets this for free from its own GET handler -- nothing to write or maintain per URI.",
      "parentUuid": "902952c1_64a715ff",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 19,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "71bedad7c8f1692d7c613474b0dfa8c4cd7c23da",
